data.message: I haven't embarrassed myself in front of a celebrity to an extent where I hated myself for doing it. I once attended a Cody Simpson concert on April 19, 2011 while attending the concert I ended up being in the front row. While Cody Simpson was singing "Don't Cry Your Heart Out" I didn't know the song so I decided to make a heart out of my hands and put them high up in the air so that he can see it. Throughout the whole song I had my hands in the shape of a heart in the air. Cody Simpson looked at me for at least 20 seconds and while he was looking at me he gave me a big dirty look like he was thinking "The hell are you doing? I see it now put your hands down." I doubt he remembers but it makes me laugh to this day. It wasn't that embarrassing of a moment but it made me feel a bit embarrassed.
